# Rule: Component Test Coverage

**Scope:** React components in `frontend/src/components/dashboard/`
(`kpi-card`, `kpi-row`, `dashboard-header`, `income-outcome-chart`,
`profit-percent-chart`).

**Rule:** Every new or modified dashboard component must ship with at
least one test verifying it renders correctly given representative
props, including loading and/or empty-data states where applicable.

**Rationale:** None of the five existing dashboard components have any
test coverage (confirmed via `find components -name "*.test.*"`
returning empty), while the business logic feeding them is tested.
The layer users actually see is currently the least protected part of
the app.

**Compliant example:** A change to `profit-percent-chart.tsx` ships
alongside a new `profit-percent-chart.test.tsx` asserting it renders
the correct number of data points.

**Non-compliant example:** `kpi-card.tsx` is modified to change how
profit margin displays, with no accompanying test change.